MBOMBELA – Residents, businesses and visitors in the city have been requested to use water sparingly. Sembcorp Silulumanzi issued a notice on Tuesday that its water treatment works are being run at reduced capacity due to a break in a canal. Repairs are under way and are expected to take three to four days. In the meantime, residents are requested to save water.  ALSO SEE: Two week water disruption in KaNyamazane Residents are also requested to have leaks fixed and to report leaks to Sembcorp Silulumanzi’s control room on 013-752-6849, 086-174-5858 or 086-2-SILULU.